reviews.snippet:
The reason I’m putting this at 4 stars is because the price of the ramen is very expensive. I understand that Wagyu is expensive and especially halal meat however charging this much is unacceptable. I got yakiniku wagyu ramen set and it was tasty. The meat was tender and the broth was good.
The staff were amazing they let us use their prayer room and we were seated immediately. They greeted us very well and gave us ample time to make our choices for food.
All in all I would recommend this place to Muslims with a lot of money but if you’re on a budget go somewhere that’s vegan.

reviews.snippet:
🍜 Halal Ramen Delight in Ginza

While wandering through the vibrant streets of Ginza, I went on a mini mission—find delicious halal food. A quick Google search led me to Halal Ramen Shinjukutei, and what a find it was!

✨ The restaurant is spotless, giving off a fresh and welcoming vibe the moment you step inside. The staff? Incredibly friendly and helpful,.

If you’re in Ginza and craving halal ramen with a kick, Halal Ramen Shinjukutei is definitely worth a stop.
